the justice department is weighing whether to 
farm out to private business the work of government historians who 
furnish research ammunition for the agencys special nazihunting 
unit 
the proposal is being studied as part of the bush 
administrations effort to save money by privatizing certain 
functions performed by government workers but it has caused alarm 
in some circles that the work of the unit the office of special 
investigations will be undermined 
an official of the simon wiesenthal center the leading research 
center on the mass extermination of jews before and during world 
war ii criticized the idea saying it comes at a time when changes 
in eastern europe will give unprecedented access to nazi records 
