contracting work to the outside im afraid might be the 
signal that the government is looking to begin the process of 
paring back the work of the osi cooper said 
justice department spokesman doug tillett denied that saying 
we obviously want to make sure there is no diminution in the 
level of services provided by the osi employees 
tillett said the department is only studying the feasibility of 
hiring a private contractor to do the work the study was 
undertaken to comply with a white house office of management and 
budget directive that all agencies identify jobs that could be 
contracted out to private companies he said 
government historians are listed by omb as positions that could 
be turned over to private contractors he said 
tillett said contractors must show they can do the work for a 
price that is 10 percent lower than what it now costs the 
government 
