<TEXT>
people have been moving into mountain lion country 
in coal creek canyon west of boulder for 30 years but now there 
are enough people there that the big cats are becoming accustomed 
to them and getting bolder 
pets have been killed there before but so far this winter 
mountain lions have killed three dogs on their owners property 
one was leashed and one was in an enclosure one of the dogs was a 
labrador retriever and one a german shepherd 
the owner of a doberman pinscher heard a commotion behind his 
house and found a mountain lion attacking the dog when confronted 
by the human the cat calmly walked away the dog was hospitalized 
twenty miles from the canyon a mountain lion last week 
apparently killed three llamas at a ranch a private hunter killed 
a mountain lion in the canyon 
residents fear the next victims may be children walking to 
school bus stops before sunup prime hunting time for the big 
cats also known as cougars or pumas 
were not trying to get people paranoid but they are living 
in lion habitat they can be taught to be lion smart just as city 
kids have to be taught to be street smart if kids are too young to 
be lion smart they shouldnt be outside alone said kathi 
demarest a state wildlife biologist 
we are not going to kill lions just because people are afraid 
of them we are not going back to the 1870s when lions were killed 
for a bounty 
several hundred people live in the canyon on scattered home 
sites wildlife officials have begun a series of meetings with them 
to educate them about living in lion country 
people tell us they live in the colorado mountains because of 
the wildlife my goal is to teach people to appreciate the wildlife 
and live with it demarest said 
she estimated five to 45 pmas remain in the canyon area 
the cats are tawny colored with a black tip on the tail an 
adult can grow to more than 7 feet from nose to tip of tail and 
weigh upwards of 150 pounds its method of attack is to lie in 
ambush then leap on the back of its prey and bite through the 
skull or neck for the kill their main prey is deer 
kristi coughlon a state wildlife manager in the boulder 
district said there have been three confirmed mountain lion kills 
of dogs another dog injured and several unconfirmed pet kills and 
missing pets this winter however coyotes also take dogs and cats 
and landowners kill dogs she said 
if any of the mountain lions become aggressive toward humans 
state trackers can be brought in to kill them she said some 
people have obtained special state permits to kill cougars that 
have killed dogs 
until recent years there had never been a confirmed unprovoked 
mountain lion attack on a human in this country 
that changed with mass human encroachment upon lion habitat a 
child was killed by a lion in montana and a child was injured and 
another killed in an orange county calif wildlife refuge 
authorities said there have also been mountain lion attacks in 
arizona and texas 
parents must start taking their kids to the bus stop install 
a light at the bus stop clear brush away from the area dont let 
kids play alone near brush and install fenced play areas for 
kids demarest said 
many city people unwittingly do things that put them on a 
clear collision course with wildlife such as putting out salt 
blocks for deer she said 
theyre just setting themselves up for lion trouble she 
said 
mountain residents should bring their pets in at night along 
with pet food and not leave out garbage because it attracts wild 
animals she said 
we hope to develop a system that has lions tolerating people 
