<TEXT>
unconventional airplane designer burt 
rutan whose voyager flew around the world without refueling has 
built a new combat jet that flies in the face of the hightech 
highcost aviation design ethic 
the first test model of the new plane named ares will be 
rolled out monday at rutans scaled composites inc at mojave 
airport in the california high desert 
the plane intended to provide minimum complexity maintenance 
and acquisition costs is aimed more at foreign markets than the 
hightech us military and its expensive aircraft 
rutans scaled composites developed the jet for about 2 
million a fraction of the normal development cost of a military 
plane 
designed as a light attack aircraft the twintailed ares is 
constructed of composite materials and powered by a single turbofan 
engine 
composites are construction materials such as graphite and epoxy 
that offer strength without the weight of traditional aviation 
metals 
the most distinctive outward feature is the rutan specialty a 
canard a small wing forward of the main wing that increases 
stability 
the name comes from the greek god of war but is used as an 
acronym for agile responsive effective support 
the jet was designed to be armed with a 25mm gun and serve a 
primary role in close air support and against helicopters it could 
also be armed with airtoair and airtoground missiles a 
twoseat version is envisioned for forward air control and training 
missions 
ares is also suggested for border patrol and reconnaissance 
duties as well as drug interdiction missions 
overseas sales are the most likely marketing option the us 
air force has its sights on highperformance highcapability jets 
like the f16 and the developing stealth aircraft technology the 
army has focused its aviation strategy on helicopters 
rutan gained worldwide fame for designing voyager the delicate 
slender airplane that his brother dick and copilot jeana yeager 
flew around the world nonstop on a single tank of fuel 
other planes had flown around the world by being refueled in 
flight but none had ever made it on their own 
rutan used composite carbonfiber honeycomb materials for light 
weight a canard and fuelstingy engines to give voyager the 
ability to keep itself aloft for the nineday 25000mile flight 
in december 1986 
</TEXT>
