ties broken in 1967 acknowledges the error of the decision to 
sever them and its consequences including an antisemitic purge in 
1968 
all warsaw pact nations except romania cut diplomatic relations 
with israel after the 1967 middle east war when israel occupied 
arab territory poland will be the second country to restore ties 
after hungary which took the step last september 
polishisraeli relations have steadily improved since 1986 when 
each country established an interest section in the others 
capital the interest sections initially maintained through a 
second country with full diplomatic standing were elevated to 
diplomatic missions on jan 1 1989 
the period of abnormality in our contacts is over and now we 
should simply embark on building the new structure of relations and 
fill it with concrete contents mordechai palzur head of the 
israeli mission in warsaw told the zycie warszawy newspaper last 
week 
