<TEXT>
negotiators for the united steelworkers of 
america and ltv steel have reached a tentative labor agreement that 
could avert a strike officials said 
union spokesman gary hubbard said the agreement approved early 
sunday by union negotiators also must be approved by the unions 
international executive board by almost 13000 steelworkers 
employed by ltv and by a us bankruptcy court judge 
parent ltv corp filed for chapter 11 bankruptcy protection in 
july 1986 listing 6 billion in assets making it one of the 
countrys biggest industrial bankruptcies 
terms of the agreement which was agreed to take effect sunday 
were not released 
in a statement the union said it expected the executive board 
to act quickly on the pact but did not say when the board would 
meet 
the new labor agreement is competitive with recent settlements 
between the steelworkers and other domestic steelmakers said 
david h hoag ltv steels president and chief executive officer 
however it has several unique features including the 
establishment of a joint customer satisfaction initiative that will 
involve the entire ltv steel work force in our effort to 
continuously improve our quality and customer service 
steelworkers employed at 13 ltv locations will vote by mail via 
secret ballot the union said the vote will not take place until 
the agreement is considered by burton lifland the bankruptcy judge 
who is supervising ltvs reorganization 
ltv produces engineered flat rolled and tubular steel products 
and is a wholly owned subsidiary of ltv corp a manufacturing 
company also involved in aerospace defense and energy products 
